  "title": "Investment Advisory Intern",
  "description": "<p>Your role is to assist Senior Directors in identifying market opportunities, sales and analyze how investment products fit into a client’s long-term protection and legacy planning.<br /><br /><strong>Job Description</strong></p><p><strong>1. Investment Research & Analysis</strong><br />Analyze financial products to assess their risk-return profiles.<br />Conduct fundamental and quantitative research on various financial assets.<br />Monitor global market trends and summarize their impact on client portfolios.<br />Perform competitor analysis and benchmarking of different investment products.</p><p><strong>2. Portfolio Support & Reporting</strong><br />Assist in the preparation of financial and investment proposal decks and monthly portfolio performance reviews.<br />Assist in preparing financial portfolio summaries that consolidate a client's existing portfolio, coverage gaps, and investment performance.<br />Draft investment proposals tailored to specific life stages (e.g., education planning for children or retirement legacy).<br /><br /><strong>3. Client & Sales Operation</strong><br />Shadowing client meetings to record minutes and track follow-up actions (e.g., account opening, KYC documentation).<br />Assisting in onboarding of clients<br />Track sales performance data and incentive tiers for the team<br /><br /><strong>Why Join Us! </strong></p><p>You will work in a dynamic environment under senior leadership.  You will be guided and learn the art of persuasion, develop professional resilience, and build a high-value network of industry leaders. This role will enable you to learn how to solve real-world business problems and understanding the mechanics of financial, sales and investment strategies.</p>",
